<script><![CDATA[function onAfter(current, previous) {
	//This function will be automatically called when this rule is processed.
	//updated
	var debug = gs.getProperty('byu.updateSet.debug');
	var instanceName = gs.getProperty('instance_name');
	if(debug) {
		gs.log("Collisions = " + current.collisions, "DevOps Pipeline - Commit Update Set");
	}
	if(current.collisions == 0) {
		if(instanceName == "byutest" && current.u_push_to_test == true) {
			if(debug) {
				gs.log("Committing Code", "DevOps Pipeline - Commit Update Set");
			}
			commitCode();
		} else if (instanceName == "byu" && current.u_push_to_prod == true) {
			if(debug) {
				gs.log("Committing Code", "DevOps Pipeline - Commit Update Set");
			}
			var standardChange = '1362f96858769140929ca41995ea6c84';
			var ajaz = new StandardChangeAJAX();
			var change = ajaz.createChange(standardChange);
			var cr = new GlideRecord('change_request');
			if(cr.get(change)){
				var engTaskSysId = getEngTask();
				if(engTaskSysId){
					createRelatedTaskRecord(engTaskSysId, cr.sys_id);
				}
				cr.state = "20";
				cr.sys_created_by = current.u_completed_by.user_name;
				cr.short_description = "ServiceNow: " + current.name;
				cr.description += "\nNotes: " + current.description;
				cr.work_start = gs.nowDateTime();
				cr.u_requested_date = gs.now();
				assignChangeTask(cr.sys_id);
				cr.update();
				cr.watch_list += "," + current.u_notify_users;
				cr.assigned_to = current.u_completed_by;
				cr.requested_by = current.u_completed_by;
				cr.update();
				commitCode();
				cr.state = "50";
				cr.work_end = gs.nowDateTime();
				cr.u_completion_rating = "1";
				cr.closed_by = current.u_completed_by;
				cr.update();
				closeTask(engTaskSysId, cr.number);
			} else {
				var shortDescChange = "ERROR with Finding Standard Change Request for update set:" + current.sys_id;
				var descChange = "Couldn't find the standard change: " + standardChange + " didn't finish the commit of update set " + current.name + ".  Please review and close task.";
				createEngTask(shortDescChange, descChange);
				gs.log("Couldn't find standard change request of sysId = " + standardChange, "DevOps Pipeline - Commit Update Set");
			}
		}
	} else {
		//Make Eng Task because of the collisions
		var link = "";
		if(instanceName == "byutest") {
			link = "https://ittest.byu.edu/nav_to.do?uri=sys_remote_update_set.do?sys_id=" + current.sys_id;
		} else if(instanceName == "byu"){
			link = "https://it.byu.edu/nav_to.do?uri=sys_remote_update_set.do?sys_id=" + current.sys_id;
		}
		var shortDesc = 'ERROR with Automatic Commit of Update Set: ' + current.name;
		var desc = 'A recent update set was not able to be committed please go and check out what the issue was on instance:' + instanceName + '.  Link = ' + link;
		if(current.u_push_to_test == true){
			createEngTask(shortDesc, desc);
		}
	}
}

function getEngTask() {
	var eng = new GlideRecord('task');
	eng.addQuery('number', current.u_task);
	eng.query();
	if(eng.next()) {
		return eng.sys_id;
	}
}

function closeTask(taskSysId, rfcNumber) {
	if(current.u_close_task == true) {
		var eng = new GlideRecord('task');
		if(eng.get(taskSysId)){
			if(eng.sys_class_name == "u_lr_release_task"){
				eng.state = "51";
			} else if (eng.sys_class_name == "u_eng_task"){
				eng.state = "3";
			}
			eng.u_task_work_log = "Automatically closed due to completion of " + rfcNumber;
			eng.closed_by = current.u_completed_by;
			eng.update();
		}
	}
}

function createRelatedTaskRecord(rfc, task) {
	var related = new GlideRecord('u_m2m_related_tasks');
	related.initalize();
	related.u_task_1 = rfc;
	related.u_task_2 = task;
	related.insert();
}

function assignChangeTask(rfcSysId) {
	var change = new GlideRecord('change_task');
	change.addQuery('change_request', rfcSysId);
	change.query();
	if(change.next()){
		change.assigned_to = current.u_completed_by;
		change.update();
	}
}

function createEngTask(shortDesc, desc) {
	var cet = new CreateEngineerTask();
	cet.createTask(shortDesc, desc);
}

function commitCode(){
	//Commit the code
	//Load the remote update set and create a local updateset from it.
	var debug = gs.getProperty('byu.updateSet.debug');
	var remote_updateset = new GlideRecord('sys_remote_update_set');
	remote_updateset.addQuery('sys_id', current.sys_id);
	remote_updateset.query();
	if ( remote_updateset.next() ) {
		var worker = new GlideUpdateSetWorker();
		// inserts the new local update set and updates the remote update set accordingly
		var lus = new GlideRecord('sys_update_set');
		if (!lus.canWrite() )
			return 0;
		
		var lus_sysid = worker.remoteUpdateSetCommit(lus, remote_updateset, remote_updateset.update_source.url);
		copyUpdateXML(lus_sysid, remote_updateset.sys_id);
		remote_updateset.update();
		
		worker.setUpdateSetSysId(lus_sysid);
		worker.setProgressName(gs.getMessage("Committing update set: {0}", remote_updateset.name));
		worker.setBackground(false);
		worker.start();
		if(debug) {
			gs.log("Worker Started", "DevOps Pipeline - Commit Update Set");
		}
	}
}

function copyUpdateXML(lsysid, rsysid) {
	var xgr = new GlideRecord("sys_update_xml");
	xgr.addQuery("remote_update_set", rsysid);
	if (updateSetPreviewInstalled()) {
		var pgr = new GlideRecord("sys_update_preview_xml");
		pgr.addQuery("remote_update.remote_update_set",rsysid);
		pgr.query();
		while (pgr.next()) {
			if (pgr.proposed_action != "skip")
				continue;
			var temp = new GlideRecord("sys_update_xml");
			temp.query("sys_id", pgr.remote_update);
			if (temp.next())
				xgr.addQuery("name","!=", temp.name +"");
		}
	}
	xgr.query();
	while(xgr.next()) {
		var lxgr = new GlideRecord("sys_update_xml");
		lxgr.initialize();
		lxgr.name = xgr.name;
		lxgr.payload = xgr.payload;
		lxgr.action = xgr.action;
		lxgr.type = xgr.type;
		lxgr.target_name = xgr.target_name;
		lxgr.view = xgr.view;
		lxgr.update_domain = xgr.update_domain;
		lxgr.table = xgr.table;
		lxgr.category = xgr.category;
		lxgr.application = xgr.application;
		lxgr.update_set = lsysid;
		if (lxgr.isValidField('replace_on_upgrade'))
			lxgr.replace_on_upgrade = xgr.replace_on_upgrade;
		lxgr.insert();
	}
}]]></script>

	getContractForAccount: function(){
		var acc = this.getParameter("sysparm_sys_id");
	//gs.info('account'+acc);
	var contract = new GlideRecord("ast_contract");
			contract.addQuery("account", acc);
			contract.query();
			if(contract.getRowCount() == 1){
				contract.next();
				return contract.getValue("sys_id");
			}
		
	},
	
	getCustomerForAccount: function()
	{
		var acc = this.getParameter("sysparm_sys_id");
		var rel = new Gliderecord('account_relationship');
		//to_company=f9823eefdb3333006fedf53a29961993^relationship_label=Is Customer Of
		rel.addQuery('to_company',acc);
		rel.addQuery('relationship_label','Is Customer Of');
		rel.query();
		while(rel.next())
			{
				//from_company=2d04c7e3dbb333006fedf53a299619d9
				return rel.getValue('from_company');
			}
		
		
		
	},

<script><![CDATA[function onBefore(current, previous) {
	//This function will be automatically called when this rule is processed.
	var debug = gs.getProperty('byu.updateSet.debug');
	var instanceName = gs.getProperty('instance_name');
	if(instanceName == "byutest"){
		//If its on test its calling build
		gs.log("Test calling to update fields", "DevOps Pipeline - Get Values Downstream");
		getValues('UpdateSetsBuild');
	}
	if(instanceName == "byu"){
		//If its on prod its calling test
		gs.log("Prod calling to update fields", "DevOps Pipeline - Get Values Downstream");
		getValues('UpdateSetsTest');
	}
}

function getValues(soapCall) {
	try {
			var s = new sn_ws.SOAPMessageV2(soapCall, 'get');
			s.setStringParameter('sys_id', current.remote_sys_id);
			var response = s.execute();
			var responseBody = response.getBody();
			var status = response.getStatusCode();
			if(status == 200) {
				var xml = new XMLDocument(responseBody);
				current.u_push_to_prod = xml.getNodeText("//getResponse//u_push_to_prod");
				current.u_push_to_test = xml.getNodeText("//getResponse//u_push_to_test");
				current.sys_created_by = xml.getNodeText("//getResponse//sys_created_by");
				current.u_completed_by = xml.getNodeText("//getResponse//completed_by");
				current.u_task = xml.getNodeText("//getResponse//u_task");
				current.u_close_task = xml.getNodeText("//getResponse//u_close_task");
				current.u_notify_users = xml.getNodeText("//getResponse//u_notify_users");
				gs.log("Saving changes of pushes in the retrieved update sets-test", "DevOps Pipeline - Get Values Downstream");
			}
		}
		catch(ex) {
			var message = ex.getMessage();
		}
